# Arduino LED Blink Project

## Overview
This project demonstrates the basic operation of an Arduino Uno by blinking an LED at one-second intervals. It is one of the fundamental projects for learning Arduino programming and digital output control.

## Components Required
- Arduino Uno R3
- LED
- 220 Ω Resistor
- Jumper Wires

## Circuit Connections
| Arduino Pin | Component |
|-------------|-----------|
| Digital Pin 13 | LED Anode (+) |
| GND | LED Cathode (-) through a 220 Ω resistor |

## Arduino Code

```cpp
void setup()
{
  pinMode(13, OUTPUT);
}

void loop()
{
  digitalWrite(13, HIGH);
  delay(1000);

  digitalWrite(13, LOW);
  delay(1000);
}
```

## Working Principle
- The LED connected to digital pin 13 is configured as an output.
- The LED turns ON for 1 second.
- The LED turns OFF for 1 second.
- This process repeats continuously, creating a blinking effect.

## Output
The LED blinks repeatedly with a delay of one second between the ON and OFF states.

## Software Used
- Arduino IDE
- Tinkercad Circuits

